    "attributes": {
        "action": "Give all 2021 A-level students grades based on their GCSE results",
        "additional_details": "During the summer 2020 lockdown, all students received different qualities of teaching. Some being given fantastic support and some being given barely at all! Majority of 2021 students have not been given the chance to sit a mock exam or formal examination of any sort and therefore to base students\u2019 grades off \u2018topic assessments\u2019 that \u2018do not matter\u2019 is simply unfair and incredibly dangerous for our futures.",
        "background": "All students\u2019 A-level results should be based off their GCSE results.",
