        "other_parliamentary_business": [
            {
                "body": "Ofqual and the Department for Education have launched a consultation on how GCSE, AS and A level grades should be awarded in summer 2021. They'd like to hear from students who were due to take their exams, their parents and carers, their teachers, school and college leaders and others who have an interest, including further and higher education providers, and employers. \nThe consultation outlines proposals for grades based on teacher assessment, and asks for views on these, including how teachers should be supported to make their assessments fairly and consistently. \nYou can find out more about the consultation and contribute here: https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/consultation-on-how-gcse-as-and-a-level-grades-should-be-awarded-in-summer-2021  \nThe consultation closes at 11:45pm on 29 January 2021. \n",
                "created_at": "2021-01-19T15:06:03.782Z",
                "subject": "Share your views on how GCSE, AS and A level grades should be awarded in summer 2021",
